Variable descriptions are as follows: format : col name - description

  1. Title - The title of the movie. (source: IMDB)
  2. LifetimeGross - The domestic lifetime gross of the movie in USD (not accounting inflation). (source: Box Office Mojo)
  3. contentR - The category based on the movie suitability for audience. (source: Rotten Tomatoes)
  4. Year - The year of movie release. (source: IMDB)
  5. Runtime - The movie run time in minutes. (source: IMDB)
  6. imdbR - The IMDB rating from 1 to 10, average of user votes. (source: IMDB)
  7. rottentmtR - The percentage of positive critic reviews from 1 to 100. (source: Rotten Tomatoes)
  8. imdbC - The number of votes that went into the IMDB rating. (source: IMDB)
  9. rottentmtC - The number of critic ratings counted for tomatometer rating. (source: Rotten Tomatoes)

3. Variable EDA: Slicing the Data for an Overview

3.1 Independent Variable: Lifetime Gross Overveiw

3.2 Dependent Variable

3.2.1 Content rating overview

The descriptions for content rating we are dealing with are as follows: format : Content rating - description

  1. G - For all audience. (source: IMDB)
  2. PG - Parental guidance suggested (mainly for under 10’s). (source: IMDB)
  3. PG-13 - Parental guidance suggested for children under 13. (source: IMDB)
  4. R - Under 17 not admitted without parent or guardian. (source: IMDB)
  5. NC17 - Under 17 not admitted. (source: IMDB)
  6. NR - Not been submitted for a rating or an uncut version of movie. (source: ATLAS CINEMAS)
